rComments: Jill Carter is a true gift; she is intelligent, caring and a great professor.  Her Indigenous values provide respect, participation and deeply meaningful learning.  Every university student would benefit from this course.  Her readings are amazing and inspirational sources to really learn and enjoy this course and care for her students.

Jill is wonderful, knowledgeable and empathetic. Taking Indigenous theatre with her was a mind-opening experience. She tends to ramble/get off track, but even her tangents are interesting if you're ok with going with the flow. In terms of marks, it's really just important to engage with the theories so you can follow class discussion.
Gives really theatrical, spirited (sometimes funny) lectures. You'll either really like her lectures and teaching style or think that it's total bs.
She not only turned around my university career, but my life as well. You will never forget the lessons you learn in her class. Do not take 201 if it is not with Jill.
